&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Feeling and Thinking are two different process in human &lt;br>
And both work from different parts of the human brain. &lt;br>
Metaphorically people say &lt;br>
thinking is from the head and feeling from heart.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>People say when in conflict between head and heart &lt;br>
then listen to the heart and not head.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Think deeper, ask yourself &lt;br>
can you think without feeling anything? &lt;br>
If that is possible then how it is possible that &lt;br>
you think about some past event and you become emotional?&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>